17/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's government adopted a plan Monday (16 May) for the restructuring and privatisation of the national power utility, ESM.
The cabinet approved separating ESM into two new companies -- one dealing with power generation and the other tackling distribution.
In other news Monday, Greek Deputy Foreign Minister Euripides Stylianidis met with Kosovo Trade Minister Bujar Dugoli for talks on boosting business ties.
On the agenda was the participation of Greek companies in Kosovo's privatisation drive and the government's backing for Kosovo's shift towards Europe.
(kosovareport -- 17/05/05;
Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 16/05/05)
